# Price Rounding Rules

All offer prices and sale prices MUST follow these rounding rules everywhere in the codebase:

| Value range | Rounding            |
|-------------|---------------------|
| > £50       | Nearest £5          |
| ≤ £50       | Nearest £2          |

These rules apply to **all** monetary values: sale prices, offer prices (1st, 2nd, 3rd), manual offers, voucher offers, and any derived price.

## Implementations

- **Backend**: `_round_offer_price()` and `_round_sale_price()` in [views_v2.py](mdc:pricing/views_v2.py)
- **Frontend**: `roundOfferPrice()` and `roundSalePrice()` in [helpers.js](mdc:frontend/vite-project/src/utils/helpers.js)
- **Voucher conversion**: `toVoucherOfferPrice()` in the same helpers file (applies `roundOfferPrice` after ×1.1)

Always use these centralised helpers — never do ad-hoc rounding of prices inline.
